        },
        "text_44tTYM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>“I have always believed that true beauty is not something you apply — it is something you cultivate.”<\/p><p>During his years of research in Japan, Mashiro realized that modern women rely too heavily on external solutions, while the body itself is often left unnourished.<\/p><p>Inspired by Sakura — a symbol of renewal and delicate yet resilient beauty — he set out to create something more than skincare.<\/p><p>A product that transforms not only the skin, but the way women feel about themselves.<\/p><p><em><strong>82X was born from that belief.<\/strong><\/em><\/p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
